What's the difference between picnics and cooking at home

Well, the most obvious difference is that cooking at home is much more convenient and comfortable, because you have easy access to all the ingredients and kitchen equipment you need.
In contrast, cooking during a pinic can be quite challenging. You usually have limited tools and ingredients, so you need to plan everything carefully in advance and be flexibile an make do with what you have.
Another difference is the overall experience. Cooking at home is more relaxing and routine, whereas pinics are more about enjoying the outdoor atmosphere and spending quality time with friends and family, even if the cooking process is less convenient.

Who does the cooking in your family? Why?
Definitely my mom. She's in charge of all the cooking in my family because she's really passionate about it. She always makes an effort to prepare a variety of dishes for each meal, which I really enjoy.
That said, my dad sometimes helps out, especially when we have a family fathering. He usually takes care of the grilling, so he's responsible for the barbecue.

Did you learn how to cook when you were younger
Fortunately, yes. When I was a little boy, I used to spend time in the kitchen helping my grandmother with small tasks. From that experience, I picked up a few simple recipes and basic cooking techniques. She also taught me how to decorate dishes using vegetables, which made the food look more visually appealing.
